Clearing the readOnly state of a file fails in the native code: 
CoreFileSystemLibrary.setReadOnly(...).

A correct error status is returned but ignored in Resources.setReadOnly:

	public void setReadOnly(boolean readonly) {
		IPath location = getLocation();
		if (location != null)
			CoreFileSystemLibrary.setReadOnly(location.toOSString(), readonly);
	}
